  "texts": [
    "Researchers have focused on GNNs, proposing hierarchical graph contrastive learning frameworks to explore complex intra-and inter-modal relationships 12.",
    "The study of flexible GNNs makes sense when it relates to propaganda detection.",
    "Currently, there is limited research on this topic.",
    "The inclusion of a variety of propaganda techniques, such as logical fallacies, doubt, and repetition 9, presents several challenges when using existing GNN-based methods for detecting propaganda.",
    "Propaganda detection benefits from multilevel 13, task-based neural architectures trained on Graph Convolutional neural Networks (GCN) for sentence analysis 14, as well as SpanBERT, which integrates three jointly trained classifiers for sentences, start, and end points 15."
